  {
    "id": "ChIJb48XuyTwwIcR8PIUVnwd3H8",
    "name": "Penn Valley Off Leash Dog Park",
    "businessType": "Dog Park",
    "description": "Situated within the historic and expansive Penn Valley Park, the Penn Valley Off Leash Dog Park offers a scenic and spacious retreat for city dogs right in the heart of Kansas City. Spanning 2.7 acres near the iconic Liberty Memorial and the National World War I Museum, this park combines urban convenience with breathtaking views of the downtown skyline, creating a unique backdrop for playtime. The facility is fully fenced and features double-gated entries for added security, along with separate sections for large and small dogs to ensure safe socialization. Its central location makes it a popular gathering spot for locals and urban dwellers, where dogs can run freely across the grassy terrain while owners enjoy the historic ambiance and green space of one of the city's oldest parks. The park's terrain varies, offering flat areas for running and some gentle slopes that add to the exercise for energetic pets.\n\nThe park is equipped with essential amenities to ensure a comfortable visit for everyone, including water spigots to keep pups hydrated during hot days and plenty of waste bag stations to help maintain cleanliness. While the park is best known for its open running space, it also offers a designated 1.8-acre area specifically designed for small, elderly, or handicapped dogs, ensuring inclusivity for pets of all needs and temperaments. The surrounding Penn Valley Park provides addition recreational opportunities, from paved walking trails to skate parks, making it easy to turn a quick dog park trip into a full afternoon of outdoor activity. You can find specific park rules on the [KC Parks Penn Valley page](https://kcparks.org/places/penn-valley-park-off-leash-dog-park/). For comprehensive guides on other dog-friendly spots in Missouri and to plan your next adventure, visit [Indoor Dog Park](https://www.indoordogpark.org/).",
