  {
    "id": "ChIJvXTrOkz3wIcRO47LypXxOT8",
    "name": "Waggin' Trail Dog Park",
    "businessType": "Dog Park",
    "description": "Waggin' Trail Dog Park stands out as a beloved community gem in North Kansas City, offering a generous 4.7 acres of safe, off-leash fun that caters to dogs of all sizes and energy levels. This impeccably maintained park is divided into two distinct fenced areas—one specifically for large breeds and another for small dogs—ensuring a comfortable and secure environment for every visitor. The park is particularly famous among locals for its paved walking trail that loops through the grounds, allowing owners to get their daily steps in while their dogs explore the terrain. Agility obstacles, including tunnels, jumps, and ramps, are scattered throughout the park to challenge active pups both mentally and physically, while vast open green spaces provide ample room for spirited games of fetch and social play. Thoughtful amenities like water fountains for both dogs and humans (available seasonally), reliable waste stations, and shaded benches make it a convenient and stress-free spot for daily visits.\n\nCleanliness and safety are consistently top priorities at Waggin' Trail, with regular maintenance by the city keeping the grounds in excellent condition year-round. The park's welcoming and friendly atmosphere fosters a strong sense of community, making it a fantastic place to meet fellow dog owners and share tips on pet care. While there are no restrooms immediately on-site, the park's convenient location near residential areas and dedicated parking lot make it easily accessible for residents and visitors alike. Whether you are training your dog on the agility course or just looking for a relaxing afternoon outing, this park delivers a top-tier off-leash experience. For official rules and updates, check the [KC Parks website](https://kcparks.org/places/waggin-trail-off-leash-dog-park/), and to discover other top-rated dog parks in the area, be sure to check out [Indoor Dog Park](https://www.indoordogpark.org/).",
