  {
    "id": "ChIJM8WGj87lwIcRPPtuMXRFS18",
    "name": "Swope Dog Park",
    "businessType": "Dog Park",
    "description": "Nestled within the historic and sprawling Swope Park, Swope Dog Park provides a fantastic five-acre off-leash haven for Kansas City's canine residents. This fully fenced facility is thoughtfully divided into two distinct sections: a spacious four-acre area for large dogs to romp and run, and a designated one-acre area for small dogs or those who prefer a gentler playstyle. The park's terrain is a mix of grassy fields and shaded wooded areas, offering plenty of variety for exploration. A crushed limestone loop trail circles the main area, providing a perfect path for owners to walk while keeping an eye on their pets as they socialize and play.\n\nSwope Dog Park is equipped with excellent amenities to ensure a comfortable visit, including drinking fountains for both people and pets, benches for relaxation, and waste stations to keep the area clean. The large mature trees provide ample shade during the warmer months, making it a pleasant destination year-round. Its location within Swope Park—often called the jewel of the Kansas City park system—means you are just steps away from other major attractions like the Kansas City Zoo and Starlight Theatre, allowing you to easily plan a full day of fun. Whether you are a local regular or just passing through, this park offers a safe and welcoming environment for dogs of all sizes. Visit the [official Swope Park page](https://kcparks.org/places/swope-park-off-leash-park/) for current hours and maintenance schedules. For more information on the best dog parks in the metro, visit [Indoor Dog Park](https://www.indoordogpark.org/).",
